==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro}}, from {{etyl|it}} {{term|milione||lang=it|million}}, from {{term|mille||lang=it|thousand}} (from {{etyl|la}} {{term|mille|lang=la}}) + the augmentative suffix {{term|-one|lang=it}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|[ˈmɪljən]|[ˈmɪʎən]}}, {{X-SAMPA|/"mIlj@n/}}
* {{audio|en-us-million.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{audio|En-uk-million.ogg|Audio (UK)}}
* {{rhymes|ɪljən}}
* {{hyphenation|mil|lion}}

===Cardinal numeral===
'''million'''

# {{context|[[w:Long and short scales|long and short scales]]}} The cardinal number 1,000,000: 10<sup>6</sup>.

